article.headline: CS Northridge 96, Chicago St. 85
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Jonathan Heard scored 19 of his career-high 29 points in the second half, and Calvin Chitwood had 22 points and a career-best 18 rebounds to lead Cal State Northridge to a 96-85 victory Saturday over Chicago State in the season opener for both teams. The senior Heard the Matadors' first eight points of the second half to help Northridge turn a 52-44 halftime deficit into a two-point game, 58-56. Less than two minutes later, Heard and Chitwood combined for nine points in a 12-0 run that put the Matadors ahead to stay, 72-62, with 10:08 to play. Deon Tresvant scored 14 points for the Matadors, and Paul Wayne scored 11 of his 13 points on free throws. Wayne also had six assists. David Holston scored 20 of his 29 points before 10 minutes had passed in the first half. He scored 10 points including a four-point play in the game's first 2:11, and had 23 in the first half. He fouled out with 6:44 to play. John Cantrell scored 17 points for Chicago State, Carl Montgomery scored 13 points and Tawrence Walton had 10.
